# EF Core Patterns

- Inject `ApplicationDbContext` via constructor DI — never `new` it directly
- Always `await` async EF methods (`ToListAsync`, `SaveChangesAsync`, etc.)
- Use `FindAsync(id)` for single-PK lookups; use `FirstOrDefaultAsync` when filtering
- Do not call `SaveChangesAsync` inside a loop — batch changes then save once
- Migrations live in the project, not the solution root — run `dotnet ef` from the API project directory

## Example: correct context usage in a service
```csharp
// ✅ Inject and await
public class ToDoService(ApplicationDbContext db)
{
    public async Task<ToDo?> GetByIdAsync(int id, string userId) =>
        await db.ToDos.FirstOrDefaultAsync(t => t.Id == id && t.ApplicationUserId == userId);
}

// ❌ Never instantiate DbContext manually
var db = new ApplicationDbContext(); // breaks DI lifetime management
```

## Example: adding a migration
```bash
# ✅ Run from the API project directory
dotnet ef migrations add AddDueDateIndex

# ❌ Don't run from the solution root — EF won't find the startup project
dotnet ef migrations add AddDueDateIndex  # run from todostodo/, not todostodo.sln location
```
